page.title: 19Movement in South Swanage
page.content: The only roads are in the eastern section of the block. To the west you only find footpaths, which naturally limits access so the area is rural. Cars are the main form of transport in the east. Their numbers increase greatly during the summer. Many walkers and cyclists also use the area. This area is criss-crossed with footpaths regularly used by local residents. A bus service runs daily from the town of Swanage in the north to Durlston Country Park, but this is the only form of public transport. Local taxi firms also carry residents and holidaymakers alike.
